👩‍👦 HIS MOTHER:

Age 68 , Hindu, religious, survivor of the 1971 independence war (shot with pellets).
Has survived the Independence war of Bangladesh, Bhola cyclone ( most dangerous cyclone in history)
Survived coup civil war in her country, went through the Bangladesh famine and even went through covid 19 and world war 3. Her husband left her and married a prostitute when S was only 2 months old.
Raised S by her own. Is emotional unstable and shouts a lot and doesn't trust her son due to his constant lying for no reason. Usually wouldn't listen to his son but would listens to someone else. It's a trend seen in their family.
Even if S is right about something his family would rather listens to someone else about it.
S doesn't know why and what caused them to act like that. Maybe they brushes him off as young and dumb even though he's way past of being young and is currently reaching 27 years old.

Mom's physical condition:
Weak legs, paralyzed fingers, suffers from borderline personality disorder (BPD) and anger issues. Suffers from constant muscle pain on daily basis and needs S to massage her legs every morning and before sleep. She suffers from slight insomnia.

Ex-primary school teacher with a habit of yelling; emotionally intense and deeply bonded with S.

Owns two fridges, batch cooks meals due to limited mobility.


