🦠 ZOMBIES (9 Types)

1. Skoth — mostly appeared when the outbreak first started and mostly non existent nowadays as their body started decayed 9 months after the outbreak.
Dogs are unaffected.
Cats die if they get bitten
Cows also die
Chimpanzee can become zombified but dies within weaks. Same goes for most mamals. Insects are unaffected by it.
Plants can get infected but are mostly harmless unless you eat the wood.
The fruits doesn't seems like affected by it but it dies off.
The flowers of infected trees stop producing smells


2. Glowbubs — these zombies seems to be attracted to light sources and will stare at lights unless it goes out.
One time when a group of  survivors accidentally turned off a light when getting in a broken shop
Got taken out in one go by these glowbubs and it ran to the nearest light source.


3. Jawies— have powerful jaws that can crush metal.
They can bite humans in one chew and usually seen ramping against doors of survivals. Mostly people who had big muscles as humans become like this


4. Whites — white-haired females who awaken via vibration.
They can feel the vibration from ground or floor they are standing on.
They can feel it from km away.
They can jump and has sharp hands as the fingers are calcified


5. Oldbones — old people who became zombies. As old human has weak bones and body and muscle
The zombification made their head have more meat which makes it harder to kill these oldies zombies.
Their spine gets out of their body in extremely painful way and it seems these spines are sharp enough to penetrate humans in one swipe.


6. Disabled:
Zombies who mostly people who were disabled when human
Becoming zombies make them
 - Blind — enhanced hearing.
 - Deaf — enhanced long-range sight.
 - Crippled — run using mutated limbs.


7. Noire — nocturnal ambush hunters. They mostly walk around at night
Staying extremely still unless they see movement. Doesn't matter what moved it'll rush there. Usually two or three stay together showing they have slight intelligence and hive mind behavior


8. Bloaters — emit screams that summon hordes. Their mouth is full of muscles


9. Aquatic — rare type seen walking underwater months into the outbreak.
Only one was spotted walking underwater in Paris bitting down fishes. Even though the movement are slow.
Not even water is safe it seems like.




