CHAPTER 1 (draft): STATIC SKY

Setting: Late night, S’s office in Dhaka

S yawns and stretches after hours of CAD work.

Glances at erotic billboard ad outside.

Billboard glitches to show conspiracy footage, outbreak warnings, then returns to normal.

S dismisses it as overwork hallucination.

Anni (in the Philippines) messages:

"You home yet?"

"Whiteheaded egghead ain’t letting me go yet."

"Good work today. Sleeping early. Goodnight S."

"Goodnight, Anni."

Reminisces about past partnership and bittersweet relationship.

Phone rings: his mom, who lives with him, scolds him in Bangla for being late, needing meds and dinner.

S replies he’s leaving soon.

Boss yells for him to finish work.

Finishes by 9:37 PM, exits building.

Notes shopping list for salary day tomorrow: eggs, rice, chickens, meds for mom.

Stares at moon. It glitches. Sees a strange silver shimmer.

Assumes he's hallucinating.

Voice that only readers can see : "The sky is warning him. And only him but he doesn't know it"

🏢 CHAPTER 2 draft – Office Party:

The story begins mostly normal: S’s office has a party for 4 new employees:

1 short, quiet girl

3 male hires

Boss sings terribly — tone-deaf and unbearable.

S leaves early due to this.

Scene transitions into darkness and surreal dread — something’s wrong.

After the party, strange events start happening. The environment feels unstable.

By the end of Chapter 2, S is mysteriously transferred — with dread and secrecy around it.

This may be the start of a major shift in the world or his perception

